In triangle $ABC,$ $a = 8,$ $b = 7,$ and $c = 5.$  Let $H$ be the orthocenter.

[asy]
unitsize(0.6 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F, H;

B = (0,0);
C = (8,0);
A = intersectionpoint(arc(B,5,0,180),arc(C,7,0,180));
H = orthocenter(A,B,C);
D = (A + reflect(B,C)*(A))/2;
E = (B + reflect(C,A)*(B))/2;
F = (C + reflect(A,B)*(C))/2;

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A--D,dashed);
draw(B--E,dashed);
draw(C--F,dashed);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$H$", H, SE, UnFill);

dot(H);
[/asy]

Then
\[\overrightarrow{H} = x \overrightarrow{A} + y \overrightarrow{B} + z \overrightarrow{C},\]where $x,$ $y,$ and $z$ are constants such that $x + y + z = 1.$  Enter the ordered triple $(x,y,z).$

